products.name: NaturaLamb Luxury Natural Lamb Skin Non-Latex Condoms Lubricated

extendedInfo.detail: Luxury condoms. Real skin-to-skin intimacy. Latex free (Not made with natural rubber latex). Trusted pregnancy protection. Naturalamb brand condoms are ideal for the monogamous couple who desire heightened sensitivity with trusted pregnancy protection. Contains no latex (not made with natural rubber latex) and may be used by latex sensitive people. Water-based lubricant to increase comfort and sensitivity. For pregnancy protection only - does not protect against STIs. Each condom is individually tested to help ensure reliability. Exclusive Kling-Tite band to hold condom in place. Questions, comments? Write to: Church & Dwight Consumer Relations 500 Charles Ewing Blvd., Ewing, NJ 08628. Please enclose this panel.
extendedInfo.directions: Please see complete instructions for use inside the package.  Avoid exposure to direct sunlight or storage for prolonged periods at temperatures above 100 degrees F.
extendedInfo.warnings: This product is intended to help prevent pregnancy . It does not protect against HIV infection (AIDS) and other Sexually Transmitted Infections (STIs). In order to help reduce the risk of transmission of many STIs. Including HIV infection (AIDS), use a latex condom, such as Trojan Premium Latex Condoms. See warnings and carefully follow instructions for use printed on inner side of carton. NaturaLamb brand condoms, when used properly, are highly effective against pregnancy - although no contraceptive can guarantee 100% effectiveness. Not to be used for the prevention of sexually transmitted infections (STIs). To help reduce the risk of catching or spreading many STIs, use a latex condom. Any use of naturalamb brand condoms for other than viginal intercourse can increase the potential of damage to the condom. For maximum benefits, it is important to follow the instructions for use printed on the inner side of this package. Failure to do so may result in the loss of the benefits of a condom. A new condom should be applied each and every time before any intimate contact occurs.
